From aa26942095323c4d2f7cef41cc43b1ecfd9efad9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 16:00:16 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] quartz: adapt legacy video paths for winedmo

Update DirectShow, ASF, VMR, DDraw, WMVCore, and legacy codec integration so the winegstreamer removal still supports older WMV/ASF and DirectShow playback paths.

Game coverage from the session:

- Catherine Classic WMV playback keeps stable image presentation without the periodic dim/flicker regression.

- BlazBlue games, including BlazBlue Centralfiction, keep corrected WMV orientation and presentation behavior.

- The Agarest games keep their legacy DirectShow/WMV playback paths working after the winedmo migration.

- Persona 4 Arena Ultimax can detect and play its extensionless ASF intro asset before the main menu.

- Persona 4 Golden no longer needs the SteamGameId-specific memallocator buffer cap after the generic allocator/renderer path was verified.

- WRC4 can use the alternate ASF/DMO path that fixed the first-frame/last-frame-only playback behavior.

- Ceville and older DirectShow users keep video output instead of audio-only black frames.

- Fable, Resident Evil 1 Remaster, and Ninja Gaiden Sigma retain the legacy renderer/allocator behavior needed for their movie playback paths after the winedmo switch.

- Akiba's Trip and Darksiders keep the renderer/allocator behavior needed by the SourceReader fixes without returning to the hang or flicker states.

This also wires the legacy Indeo/IYUV/MPEG/video-resizer pieces into the new media stack where the old winegstreamer path used to provide the bridge.
